<div id="review_103284507" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/103284507" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2329228-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433629372p2/2329228.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/103284507?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/2329228-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9781441779540" href="/book/show/11369847-babbitt">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=classic-lit">classic-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=other-favorites">other-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=books-i-wouldn-t-mind-owning">books-i-wouldn-t-mind-owning</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer103284507" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2910473782234679695">Though written in the 1920s, this book easily could have been written today. I&apos;m amazed by how relatable, and familiar, it felt. Lewis captures a yearning that I think many people experience, and in his pitiable, unlikable hero, he descries the fate of modernity. <br/>I&apos;d much rather have read this book than <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4671.The_Great_Gatsby' title='The Great Gatsby by F. Scott Fitzgerald' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Great Gatsby</a> in high school. It is possible, however, that I wouldn&apos;t quite of understood it. <br/>The tone, irony, and poignancy in this book really struck me. I want to write a paper about it! <br/>D</span>
  <span id="freeText2910473782234679695" style="display:none">Though written in the 1920s, this book easily could have been written today. I'm amazed by how relatable, and familiar, it felt. Lewis captures a yearning that I think many people experience, and in his pitiable, unlikable hero, he descries the fate of modernity. <br />I'd much rather have read this book than <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4671.The_Great_Gatsby" title="The Great Gatsby by F. Scott Fitzgerald" rel="nofollow noopener">The Great Gatsby</a> in high school. It is possible, however, that I wouldn't quite of understood it. <br />The tone, irony, and poignancy in this book really struck me. I want to write a paper about it! <br />Definitely one I will have to come back to in a few years. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2910473782234679695" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
